      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "Actually the javac compiler from Java 1.6 did compile such methods (with the same erasure) correctly, as long as they had different return types - see <a href=\"http://stackoverflow.com/questions/5527235/type-erasure-and-overloading-in-java-why-does-this-work\" title=\"type erasure and overloading in java why does this work\">stackoverflow.com/questions/5527235/&hellip;</a>. Unfortunately they &quot;fixed&quot; it in Java 7... :("
