      "body" : "@erickson When your class has two constructors which accept two different lists, such as <code>List&lt;String&gt;</code> and <code>List&lt;Integer&gt;</code>. They operate on the lists differently but they can not exist separately due to this error. So I need a way to define both operations within one constructor that takes just <code>List</code>. I have no idea how to check for the correct generic types and cast given <code>List</code> to <code>List&lt;Something&gt;</code> as needed."
